div1.p: In the District COurt of the United States for the Western District of Washington Northern Division
In re Gwoo Shoo Ah Look, Habeas Corpus. No. 2647
Witness my habnd and official seal this 2d day of May, 1914.
div1.ab: By Ed M Larken Deputy Clerk
div1.p: In re application of Gwoo Shoo Ah Look for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.

Now on this day this this cause comes on for hearing, the United States represented by George P. Fishburn, and attorney for petitioner no appearing, the hearing is continued on motion of the Assistant United States Attorney and upon his statement that counsel for petitioner desires a continuance to Monday, Feburary 2, 1914 at 10.00 A.M.
In the matter of the application for a Writ of Habeas Corpus for Gwoo Shoo Ah Look.

Now on this day this cause comes on for hearing, the Petitioner represented by Jesse A. Frye and the Government by G.P. Fishburn, whereupon the application of Petitioner to be admitted bail bond and amount thereof fixed is denied by the Court.
In re application of Gwoo Shoo Ah Look for Writ of Habeas Corpus.

Now on this day this cause comes on for hearing, The Petitioner being in Court and represented by his counsel Messrs. Wilbur & Spencer, and Jesse A. Frye, Esq., and the Respondent represented by Geo. F. Fishburne, whereupon Petitioner's witness A.L. Clark and Respondent's witness J.H. Barbour and duly examined, and the Court is argued by respective counsel and taked under advisement by the Court.
